<heading id="D0E3505C837F7E00A3C0F937B5C76BB9" bold="true" box="[151,1018,1709,1736]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837F7E00A3C0F937B5C76BB9" bold="true" box="[151,1018,1709,1736]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
Key to the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB3837F7E00A2CAF934B47F6BB6" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1860" baseAuthorityName="Fieber" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[413,578,1709,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837F7E00A2CAF934B47F6BB6" bold="true" box="[413,578,1709,1736]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">Megalotomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurring in the Palaearctic region
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30EB4BB837F7E03A3C0F96AB3A16CCA" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="221" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" type="key">
<keyStep id="30E0FF95837F7E00A3C0F96AB3A16A3C" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<paragraph id="8BABE730837F7E00A3C0F96AB3A16A5B" blockId="9.[151,1437,1779,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<keyLead id="30E54405837F7E00A3C0F96AB3A16A5B" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
1. Small sized, usually not surpassing 12.0 mm in length; pronotum with a conspicuous triangular or cuneiform dark black hairless region................................................................ 
<emphasis id="B9603B22837F7E00A77DF889B3A16A5B" bold="true" box="[1066,1436,1807,1830]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB3837F7E00A77DF889B3146A58" authority="(Hsiao, 1965)" authorityName="Yi &amp; Wang &amp; Zhang &amp; Bu" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Hsiao" baseAuthorityYear="1965" box="[1066,1321,1807,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837F7E00A77DF889B2A66A5B" bold="true" box="[1066,1179,1807,1829]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">M. angulus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF859AC1837F7E00A7FFF889B31C6A58" author="Hsiao, T. Y." box="[1192,1313,1808,1830]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" pagination="421 - 434" refId="ref8565" refString="Hsiao, T. Y. (1965) New Coreids from China (Hemiptera, Heteroptera) IV. Acta Zoologica Sinica, 17 (4), 421 - 434. [in Chinese, with English summary]" type="journal article" year="1965">Hsiao, 1965</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2538659837F7E00A679F889B3A16A5B" box="[1326,1436,1808,1829]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABE730837F7E00A3C0F8B7B3A16A3C" blockId="9.[151,1437,1779,2035]" box="[151,1436,1837,1859]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<keyLead id="30E54405837F7E00A3C0F8B7B3A16A3C" box="[151,1436,1837,1859]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">- Moderate or large sized, usually surpassing 12.0 mm in length; pronotum normal, without any black hairless region...... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30E0FF95837F7E00A3C0F8D2B3A16A03" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<paragraph id="8BABE730837F7E00A3C0F8D2B3A16A1E" blockId="9.[151,1437,1779,2035]" box="[151,1436,1867,1889]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<keyLead id="30E54405837F7E00A3C0F8D2B3A16A1E" box="[151,1436,1867,1889]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">2. Body almost entirely black, with vertex and pronotum consistent black........................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABE730837F7E00A3C0F8F1B3A16A03" blockId="9.[151,1437,1779,2035]" box="[151,1436,1896,1918]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<keyLead id="30E54405837F7E00A3C0F8F1B3A16A03" box="[151,1436,1896,1918]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">- Body yellowish brown or reddish brown, vertex or pronotum brownish, never entirely dark black...................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30E0FF95837F7E00A3C0F81CB3A06A8D" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<paragraph id="8BABE730837F7E00A3C0F81CB3A16AC9" blockId="9.[151,1437,1779,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<keyLead id="30E54405837F7E00A3C0F81CB3A16AC9" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
3. In male genital capsule, surcapsular spine with narrow and straight spike arising in middle, paramere split into two lobes at apex............................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB3837F7E00A79FF83AB3A16AC9" authority="Stal, 1873" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1873" box="[1224,1436,1954,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costalis">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837F7E00A79FF83AB3A16AC9" bold="true" box="[1224,1436,1954,1976]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837F7E00A79FF83AB30F6AC6" bold="true" box="[1224,1330,1954,1976]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">M. costalis</emphasis>
Stål, 1873
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABE730837F7E00A3C0F859B3A06A8D" blockId="9.[151,1437,1779,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<keyLead id="30E54405837F7E00A3C0F859B3A06A8D" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
- Surcapsular spine with small and broad projection close to the proximal part, paramere with two pointed apices at the terminal part, not divided into lobes......................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB3837F7E00A7C6F847B3A06A8D" authority="(Scopoli, 1763)" baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" box="[1169,1437,2013,2035]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="junceus">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837F7E00A7C6F847B3A06A8D" bold="true" box="[1169,1437,2013,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837F7E00A7C6F847B2C26A8C" bold="true" box="[1169,1279,2013,2035]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="220">M. junceus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF859AC1837F7E00A65BF844B3A86A8D" author="Scopoli, J. A." box="[1292,1429,2013,2035]" pageId="9" pageNumber="220" refId="ref9421" refString="Scopoli, J. A. (1763) Entomologia carniolica exhibens Insecta Carnioliae indigena et distributa in ordines, genera, species, varietatis. Methodo Linnaeana. Trattner, Vindobonae, xxxvi + 420 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 119976" type="book" year="1763">Scopoli, 1763</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30E0FF95837C7E03A3C0FF01B3A16C7B" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<paragraph id="8BABE730837C7E03A3C0FF01B3A16DB4" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,437]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="30E54405837C7E03A3C0FF01B3A16DB4" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
4. Body size large, over 15.0 mm in length; anterior lobe of pronotum black and posterior lobe reddish brown; posterior angle of pronotum acute and pointed, with a sharp apex......................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB3837C7E03A7C4FF2CB3A16DB4" authority="Reuter, 1888" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1888" box="[1171,1436,181,202]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837C7E03A7C4FF2CB3A16DB4" bold="true" box="[1171,1436,181,202]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837C7E03A7C4FF2CB3286DB4" bold="true" box="[1171,1301,181,202]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">M. castaneus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF859AC1837C7E03A64BFF2CB3A16DB4" author="Reuter, O. M." box="[1308,1436,181,202]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221" pagination="63 - 69" refId="ref9285" refString="Reuter, O. M. (1888) Hemiptera Sinensia Enumeravit ac novas species descripsit. Revue d'Entomologie, VII, 63 - 69." type="journal article" year="1888">Reuter, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABE730837C7E03A3C0FF4AB3A16C7B" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,437]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="30E54405837C7E03A3C0FF4AB3A16C7B" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">- Body size moderate, less than 15.0 mm in length; pronotum uniformly brownish; posterior angle of pronotum upturned but not acute............................................................................................... 5</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30E0FF95837C7E03A3C0FE94B3A16C3E" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<paragraph id="8BABE730837C7E03A3C0FE94B3A16C5C" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,437]" box="[151,1436,269,291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="30E54405837C7E03A3C0FE94B3A16C5C" box="[151,1436,269,291]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
5. All femora reddish yellow, with dense red speckles..................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB3837C7E03A7C7FE94B3A16C5C" authority="Kerzhner, 1972" authorityName="Kerzhner" authorityYear="1972" box="[1168,1436,269,290]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zaitzevi">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837C7E03A7C7FE94B3A16C5C" bold="true" box="[1168,1436,269,290]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837C7E03A7C7FE94B2C76C5C" bold="true" box="[1168,1274,269,290]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">M. zaitzevi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF859AC1837C7E03A657FE94B3A16C5C" author="Kerzhner, I. M." box="[1280,1436,269,290]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221" pagination="349 - 379" refId="ref8755" refString="Kerzhner, I. M. (1972) New and little-known Heteroptera from Mongolia and from adjacent regions of the USSR. I. Nasekomye Mongolii, 1, 349 - 379. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1972">Kerzhner, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABE730837C7E03A3C0FEB2B3A16C3E" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,437]" box="[151,1436,298,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="30E54405837C7E03A3C0FEB2B3A16C3E" box="[151,1436,298,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">- Femora brownish, with black punctures.................................................................... 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30E0FF95837C7E03A3C0FEDEB3A16CCA" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<paragraph id="8BABE730837C7E03A3C0FEDEB3A06C04" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,437]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="30E54405837C7E03A3C0FEDEB3A06C04" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
6. Conspicuous, light-coloured spot on forewing, shaped somewhat like a split arrow; paramere expanded apically, with 5–8 projections around apex............................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB3837C7E03A7CDFEFCB3A06C04" authority="(Stal, 1858)" baseAuthorityName="Stal" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[1178,1437,356,378]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ornaticeps">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837C7E03A7CDFEFCB3A06C04" bold="true" box="[1178,1437,356,378]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837C7E03A7CDFEFCB31E6C04" bold="true" box="[1178,1315,357,378]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">M. ornaticeps</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF859AC1837C7E03A678FEFDB3A86C04" author="Stal, C." box="[1327,1429,356,378]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221" pagination="307 - 320" refId="ref9473" refString="Stal, C. (1858) Orthoptera och Hemiptera fran sodra Afrika. Ofversigt af Kongliga Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 15, 307 - 320." type="journal article" year="1858">Stål, 1858</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABE730837C7E03A3C0FE1AB3A16CCA" blockId="10.[151,1437,151,437]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<keyLead id="30E54405837C7E03A3C0FE1AB3A16CCA" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
- Light-coloured spot small and inconspicuous, parameres tapering towards apex, without apical projections........................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C149CB3837C7E03A72CFE39B3A16CCA" authority="Liu &amp; Liu, 1998" authorityName="G. Q. Liu &amp; Q. Liu" authorityYear="1998" box="[1147,1436,415,437]" class="Insecta" family="Alydidae" genus="Megalotomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutulus">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837C7E03A72CFE39B3A16CCA" bold="true" box="[1147,1436,415,437]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis id="B9603B22837C7E03A72CFE39B2CF6CCB" bold="true" box="[1147,1266,415,437]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="221">M. acutulus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF859AC1837C7E03A7AFFE06B3A16CCA" author="Liu, G. Q. &amp; Liu, Q." box="[1272,1436,415,437]" pageId="10" pageNumber="221" pagination="41 - 44" refId="ref8869" refString="Liu, G. Q. &amp; Liu, Q. (1998) On the genus Megalotomus Fieber from China (Heteroptera: Alydidae). Entomologische Berichten, Amsterdam, 58 (3), 41 - 44." type="journal article" year="1998">Liu &amp; Liu, 1998</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
